Introducing gg_greek. A simple, symmetrical map suited towards the gungame counter-strike source mod.

The map was produced in 2 hours as part of a small mapping competition with a few friends. The theme was "Temple", so I went with this iconic greek style. Sorry to those who know, but no, the columns are not tapered.

This is the final product, with no changes to the initial 2 hours worth of work.

The map plays well, is simple to learn, and is not dominated by any specific type of weapon or playstyle.

Have fun!

About 200 miles north of Las Vegas on the dawn of a new day, two rival gangs meets at an abandoned storage facility to discuss sour business deals. As they arrive at the location both gangs find the facility enclosed and signs stating that its due for destruction. Fearing betrayal both gangs enter with nerves on the edge and guns drawn..

Most walls inside the building are destructable. The map is surrounded by an electric fence and also features a garage that can be completely blown up. To blow up the garage look for the sparks on the wall outside by the sheds. The sparks mark a hidden button.

This is the first beta version of Goodfellas Arena X.

There are no known bugs but if any are found please post here or e-mail me at deal@thehightower.net.

On top of the roofs walk off the side and you will be teleported to the adjacent rooftop. The two rooftops not by spawns also have teleports at their rear. To get to the balconies from the bottom walk into the x on the botton of the map.

All teleports have been optimized so that if someone stands on the target of the teleport there is 80% less chance players will be teleported into each other.

Has a custom soundscape.

The sky box texture was not made by me but by hipshot (www.zfight.com).

The beta2 version is already in the works so please post comments and ideas as they may make it into the map.
